#: ../../source/library/models/opinions/HK.rst:63
#: a83320c993ab463888bd99adfeb55476
msgid ""
"Unlike the SIR model with three discrete states, the HK model uses a "
"continuous opinion space. To avoid infinitely many states, we consider only "
"two cases (Figure \\ref{fig:HK}): if $\\#\\Gamma_\\epsilon=0$, the opinion "
"remains unchanged; otherwise, it is updated to the $\\epsilon$-neighbors’ "
"average."
msgstr ""
"与包含三个离散状态的SIR模型不同,HK模型使用连续的舆论空间. "
"为了避免无数州,我们只考虑两例(图\\ref{fig:HK}):如果$\\Gamma\\epsilon=0美元,则意见保持不变;否则,它会被更新到$\\epsilon$-nebors的平均值。"

